# Minimal .env for Template Users
#
# This is a streamlined configuration file containing only the essential
# variables needed to get started with this template for local development.
#
# Quick Start:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.minimal .env
# 2. Replace YOUR_* placeholders with your actual values
# 3. Run: ./scripts/setup_local_config.sh
#
# For complete configuration options, see .env.example

# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Repository Identity
# ============================================================================

# Your GitHub username or organization name
GITHUB_OWNER=YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME

# Your repository name (without the owner prefix)
GITHUB_REPO=YOUR_REPO_NAME

# Full repository identifier (usually derived from above)
GITHUB_REPOSITORY=${GITHUB_OWNER}/${GITHUB_REPO}

# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Package Identity
# ============================================================================

# The name of your Python package (as it appears on PyPI)
# Example: my-awesome-tool
PACKAGE_NAME=YOUR_PACKAGE_NAME

# The command name for your CLI tool
# Example: my-tool
CLI_NAME=YOUR_CLI_NAME

# Python module name (usually package name with underscores)
# Example: my_awesome_tool
MODULE_NAME=YOUR_MODULE_NAME

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Author Information
# ============================================================================

# These are auto-detected from your git config if not set
# Uncomment and fill in if you want to override git config values

# AUTHOR_NAME="Your Name"
# AUTHOR_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Version Information
# ============================================================================

# Package version (usually managed in pyproject.toml)
# VERSION="0.1.0"

# ============================================================================
# What's Next?
# ============================================================================
#
# This minimal configuration is sufficient for:
# - Local development and testing
# - Running the build process
# - Basic CI/CD workflows
#
# When you're ready to publish to distribution platforms, see .env.example
# for Phase 2 (Testing) and Phase 3 (Production) configuration options:
#
# Phase 2 - Testing Platforms:
# - TestPyPI
# - Snap (edge channel)
# - Docker (test repositories)
#
# Phase 3 - Production Platforms:
# - PyPI
# - Snap Store
# - Homebrew
# - Docker Hub / GHCR
# - Package managers (apt, yum, AUR, etc.)
#
# For complete documentation, see: .env.example
